// race condition is mean that

two or more thread access the same variables in way that the final result will store in variable
depends on how thread is schedule.

-> reason for the race condition:
1. two or more variables read and writes the variable at the same time.
2. the thread access the data the not atomic (it means that any thread can access the data)
 -- read modified writes
    -- where modified value depends on the previous read value.
